                <h1>How to Reduce High Background in Western Blotting</h1>
                <p>High background in western blotting can obscure results and lead to misleading conclusions. Common causes include poor blocking, inappropriate secondary antibody concentration, and inadequate washing. To minimize background, optimize the blocking buffer, reduce antibody concentrations, and increase wash times. Addressing these factors can enhance signal clarity.</p>
